[
'title'       => 'Trastevere — The Soul of Ancient Rome',
'order'       => 5,
'location'    => ['lat' => 41.8896, 'lng' => 12.4706],
'description' => 'Cross the Tiber River — Rome\'s ancient boundary — into the neighbourhood of Trastevere, whose name literally means "across the Tiber" (Trans Tiberim in Latin). This tightly woven district of golden-ochre medieval buildings, ivy-draped walls, and cobblestone alleys just wide enough for a Vespa is one of the oldest continuously inhabited neighbourhoods in Europe, settled since the Bronze Age and home during the Imperial period to a large community of Jewish merchants, Syrian traders, and Levantine craftspeople who gave the area its cosmopolitan, slightly unruly character — a character it has never entirely lost. Trastevere is at its magical best in the early evening, when the golden light turns the ochre walls amber and local families emerge for their passeggiata as the neighbourhood transitions from sleepy afternoon to vibrant social hub. Begin at the Basilica di Santa Maria in Trastevere, one of the oldest churches in Rome and built on the site where, according to tradition, oil spontaneously sprang from the ground in 38 BC — interpreted by early Christians as a miraculous sign of the coming of Christ. The basilica\'s golden 12th-century apse mosaics, illuminated on winter evenings, are among the finest medieval mosaics in existence. From here, lose yourself in the surrounding streets: the Vicolo del Cedro, the Piazza di Santa Cecilia (where the 3rd-century martyr was executed — her incorrupt body was famously discovered in 1599 and can still be seen in the church), and the terrace of the Gianicolo Hill above, which offers the finest panoramic view of Rome\'s rooftops and domes.',
'translations' => [
'es' => ['title' => 'Trastevere — el alma de la Roma antigua', 'description' => 'Cruce el río Tíber hacia el barrio de Trastevere, cuyo nombre significa literalmente "al otro lado del Tíber". Este apretado distrito de edificios medievales dorado-ocres, muros cubiertos de hiedra y callejones adoquinados es uno de los barrios habitados continuamente más antiguos de Europa. Trastevere es más mágico al anochecer, cuando la luz dorada torna las paredes ámbar y las familias locales salen a la passeggiata. Comience en la Basílica de Santa María en Trastevere, una de las iglesias más antiguas de Roma, cuyos mosaicos áureos del siglo XII en el ábside son de los mejores medievales existentes.'],
'fr' => ['title' => 'Trastevere — l\'âme de la Rome antique', 'description' => 'Traversez le Tibre pour rejoindre le quartier de Trastevere, dont le nom signifie littéralement "au-delà du Tibre". Ce quartier dense d\'immeubles médiévaux ocre dorés, de murs tapissés de lierre et de ruelles pavées est l\'un des plus anciens quartiers habités en continu d\'Europe. Trastevere est plus magique en début de soirée, quand la lumière dorée teinte les murs d\'ambre. Commencez par la Basilique de Santa Maria in Trastevere, l\'une des plus anciennes églises de Rome, dont les mosaïques dorées du XIIe siècle dans l\'abside comptent parmi les plus belles mosaïques médiévales existantes.'],
'de' => ['title' => 'Trastevere — die Seele des antiken Roms', 'description' => 'Überqueren Sie den Tiber in das Viertel Trastevere, dessen Name buchstäblich "jenseits des Tibers" bedeutet. Dieses dicht gewebte Viertel aus golden-ockerfarbenen mittelalterlichen Gebäuden, efeubedeckten Mauern und Kopfsteinpflastergassen ist eines der ältesten kontinuierlich bewohnten Viertel Europas. Trastevere ist am frühen Abend am zauberhaftesten. Beginnen Sie in der Basilika Santa Maria in Trastevere, einer der ältesten Kirchen Roms, deren goldene Apsismosaiken aus dem 12. Jahrhundert zu den schönsten mittelalterlichen Mosaiken überhaupt gehören.'],
'it' => ['title' => 'Trastevere — l\'anima della Roma antica', 'description' => 'Attraversate il Tevere verso il quartiere di Trastevere, il cui nome significa letteralmente "oltre il Tevere". Questo fitto quartiere di edifici medievali color ocra dorato, muri ricoperti d\'edera e vicoli acciottolati è uno dei quartieri abitati in modo continuativo più antichi d\'Europa. Trastevere è più magica nelle prime ore serali, quando la luce dorata tinge di ambra i muri. Iniziate dalla Basilica di Santa Maria in Trastevere, una delle chiese più antiche di Roma, i cui mosaici dorati dell\'abside del XII secolo sono tra i più bei mosaici medievali esistenti.'],
],
