[
'title'       => 'Basílica de Santa Maria del Mar — The People\'s Cathedral',
'order'       => 5,
'location'    => ['lat' => 41.3840, 'lng' => 2.1815],
'description' => 'From the Gothic Quarter, walk east into the El Born district to reach what many architects and architectural historians regard as the most perfect Gothic building in Spain and one of the finest in all of Europe: the Basílica de Santa Maria del Mar. What makes this church exceptional — architecturally, historically, and emotionally — is not just its beauty but its story. Unlike virtually every great medieval church, which was built over centuries by professional craftsmen under royal or ecclesiastical patronage, Santa Maria del Mar was conceived, funded, and physically built by the ordinary people of the Ribera neighbourhood — the longshoremen, fishermen, traders, and craftspeople of Barcelona\'s medieval waterfront quarter. Construction lasted just 55 years, from 1329 to 1384 — extraordinarily fast for a building of this scale and quality — because the entire community invested in it: the porters (bastaixos) who loaded and unloaded ships in the nearby port volunteered their time to carry the massive blocks of Montjuïc sandstone from the royal quarry to the building site on their backs, a fact commemorated in carvings on the main entrance doors. The result is a building of extraordinary architectural unity — because it was designed by a single master builder, Berenguer de Montagut, and built continuously to his plan — with a spare, luminous interior of three equal-height aisles separated by impossibly slender octagonal columns that create a forest of stone flooded with golden light from the enormous stained glass windows. During the War of Spanish Succession in 1714, the Bourbon forces destroyed the entire neighbourhood of the Ribera — 1,000 houses and 12 streets — to build a military fortress, the Ciutadella. The church survived, and a monument in the square in front of it commemorates the men and women of Barcelona who died defending the city that year.',
'translations' => [
'es' => ['title' => 'Basílica de Santa María del Mar — la catedral del pueblo', 'description' => 'Desde el Barrio Gótico, camine hacia el este hasta el barrio de El Born para llegar a lo que muchos arquitectos e historiadores consideran el edificio gótico más perfecto de España: la Basílica de Santa María del Mar. Lo que hace excepcional a esta iglesia es su historia: fue concebida, financiada y físicamente construida por la gente ordinaria del barrio de la Ribera — los portuarios, pescadores, comerciantes y artesanos del frente marítimo medieval de Barcelona. La construcción duró solo 55 años, de 1329 a 1384, porque toda la comunidad invirtió en ella: los bastaixos trasladaban los bloques de piedra arenisca de Montjuïc en sus espaldas desde la cantera al sitio de construcción.'],
'fr' => ['title' => 'La Basílica de Santa Maria del Mar — la cathédrale du peuple', 'description' => 'Du Quartier Gothique, marchez vers l\'est jusqu\'au quartier d\'El Born pour atteindre ce que de nombreux architectes et historiens considèrent comme l\'édifice gothique le plus parfait d\'Espagne : la Basílica de Santa Maria del Mar. Ce qui rend cette église exceptionnelle, c\'est son histoire : elle fut conçue, financée et physiquement construite par les gens ordinaires du quartier de la Ribera — les débardeurs, pêcheurs, commerçants et artisans du front de mer médiéval de Barcelone. La construction ne dura que 55 ans, de 1329 à 1384, parce que toute la communauté y investit.'],
'de' => ['title' => 'Basílica de Santa Maria del Mar — die Kathedrale des Volkes', 'description' => 'Vom Gotischen Viertel aus gehen Sie nach Osten in das Viertel El Born, um zu dem zu gelangen, was viele Architekten und Architekturhistoriker als das vollkommenste gotische Gebäude Spaniens betrachten: die Basílica de Santa Maria del Mar. Was diese Kirche außergewöhnlich macht, ist ihre Geschichte: Sie wurde von gewöhnlichen Menschen des Ribera-Viertels konzipiert, finanziert und gebaut — den Hafenarbeitern, Fischern und Handwerkern des mittelalterlichen Hafenviertels von Barcelona. Der Bau dauerte nur 55 Jahre, von 1329 bis 1384, weil die gesamte Gemeinschaft darin investierte.'],
'it' => ['title' => 'Basílica de Santa Maria del Mar — la cattedrale del popolo', 'description' => 'Dal Barrio Gótico, camminate verso est nel quartiere di El Born per raggiungere quello che molti architetti e storici dell\'architettura considerano il più perfetto edificio gotico di Spagna: la Basílica de Santa Maria del Mar. Ciò che rende questa chiesa eccezionale è la sua storia: fu concepita, finanziata e fisicamente costruita dalla gente comune del quartiere della Ribera — gli scaricatori di porto, i pescatori, i commercianti e gli artigiani del fronte marittimo medievale di Barcellona. La costruzione durò solo 55 anni, dal 1329 al 1384, perché l\'intera comunità vi investì.'],
],
],
[
'title'       => 'Mercat de Santa Caterina — The Mosaic Market',
'order'       => 6,
'location'    => ['lat' => 41.3856, 'lng' => 2.1793],
'description' => 'A ten-minute walk north of Santa Maria del Mar brings you to one of Barcelona\'s most visually arresting buildings and one of its best food markets: the Mercat de Santa Caterina, designed by the architect Enric Miralles (with Benedetta Tagliabue) and completed posthumously in 2005, three years after Miralles\'s death from a brain tumour at the age of 45. The market\'s undulating roof is covered in a mosaic of 325,000 hexagonal ceramic tiles in a riotous explosion of colours — reds, oranges, yellows, greens, blacks, whites — that represents a stylised aerial view of the fruit and vegetables sold below, and has become one of Barcelona\'s most distinctive and photographed landmarks. The building replaces a 19th-century iron market that occupied the site of the former Convent of Santa Caterina, demolished in 1837, whose foundations were discovered during construction — the archaeological remains are now visible through glass panels in the market floor. Inside, the market functions as a genuine neighbourhood food market serving local residents: fish, meat, charcuterie, cheese, fresh pasta, fruit, vegetables, flowers, herbs, and spices of excellent quality at reasonable prices. This is where the residents of El Born and the Barrio Gótico do their real shopping, and the market retains a lived-in, working character that many of Barcelona\'s more tourist-oriented food halls have lost. The surrounding neighbourhood has excellent independent restaurants, wine bars, and cocktail bars for lunch or dinner after your tour.',
'translations' => [
'es' => ['title' => 'Mercat de Santa Caterina — el mercado mosaico', 'description' => 'A diez minutos a pie al norte de Santa María del Mar se encuentra uno de los edificios más llamativos de Barcelona: el Mercat de Santa Caterina, diseñado por el arquitecto Enric Miralles y completado póstumamente en 2005. El ondulante techo del mercado está recubierto con un mosaico de 325.000 baldosas de cerámica hexagonales en una explosión de colores que representa una vista aérea estilizada de la fruta y verdura que se vende abajo. En el interior, el mercado funciona como un auténtico mercado alimentario del barrio con pescado, carne, charcutería, queso y verduras de excelente calidad a precios razonables.'],
'fr' => ['title' => 'Le Mercat de Santa Caterina — le marché mosaïque', 'description' => 'À dix minutes à pied au nord de Santa Maria del Mar se trouve l\'un des bâtiments les plus visuellement saisissants de Barcelone : le Mercat de Santa Caterina, conçu par l\'architecte Enric Miralles et achevé à titre posthume en 2005. Le toit ondulant du marché est recouvert d\'une mosaïque de 325 000 carreaux de céramique hexagonaux dans une explosion de couleurs représentant une vue aérienne stylisée des fruits et légumes vendus en dessous. À l\'intérieur, le marché fonctionne comme un véritable marché alimentaire de quartier avec poisson, viande, charcuterie, fromages et légumes d\'excellente qualité à des prix raisonnables.'],
'de' => ['title' => 'Mercat de Santa Caterina — der Mosaikmarkt', 'description' => 'Zehn Gehminuten nördlich von Santa Maria del Mar befindet sich eines der visuell beeindruckendsten Gebäude Barcelonas: der Mercat de Santa Caterina, entworfen vom Architekten Enric Miralles und 2005 posthum fertiggestellt. Das gewellte Dach des Marktes ist mit einem Mosaik aus 325.000 sechseckigen Keramikfliesen in einem explosiven Farbenrausch bedeckt, der eine stilisierte Vogelperspektive des darunter verkauften Obsts und Gemüses darstellt. Im Inneren funktioniert der Markt als echter Stadtteillebensmittelmarkt mit Fisch, Fleisch, Wurstwaren, Käse und Gemüse in ausgezeichneter Qualität zu vernünftigen Preisen.'],
'it' => ['title' => 'Mercat de Santa Caterina — il mercato mosaico', 'description' => 'A dieci minuti a piedi a nord di Santa Maria del Mar si trova uno degli edifici visivamente più sorprendenti di Barcellona: il Mercat de Santa Caterina, progettato dall\'architetto Enric Miralles e completato postumo nel 2005. Il tetto ondulato del mercato è ricoperto da un mosaico di 325.000 piastrelle esagonali in ceramica in un\'esplosione di colori che rappresenta una vista aerea stilizzata di frutta e verdura venduta al di sotto. All\'interno, il mercato funziona come un vero mercato alimentare di quartiere con pesce, carne, salumi, formaggi e verdure di eccellente qualità a prezzi ragionevoli.'],
],
],
],
];

