'location'    => ['lat' => 52.3752, 'lng' => 4.8840],
'description' => 'Begin at the Anne Frank House on the Prinsengracht — one of the most visited and most emotionally powerful museum experiences in Europe, and a place that distils the horror and the humanity of the Holocaust into a single ordinary Amsterdam merchant\'s house that is anything but ordinary. On 6 July 1942, thirteen-year-old Anne Frank, her parents Otto and Edith, and her sister Margot went into hiding in the "Secret Annexe" — a concealed rear extension of the building at Prinsengracht 263, sealed behind a movable bookcase — to escape the Nazi occupation that had been systematically stripping Dutch Jews of their rights since 1940. They were joined by four other Jewish families, eight people in total, who lived in the annexe for 761 days without stepping outside, sustained by the courage and ingenuity of the non-Jewish employees who hid and supplied them at mortal risk to themselves. On 4 August 1944, the annexe was raided by the Gestapo — still unknown who betrayed them — and all eight occupants were arrested and deported. Anne died of typhus in Bergen-Belsen concentration camp in February or March 1945, just weeks before the camp was liberated by British forces. She was 15. Only Otto Frank survived the war. He arranged the publication of Anne\'s diary, which she had kept throughout the 761 days in hiding, and which has since been translated into 70 languages and sold over 30 million copies. The diary is not just a historical document — it is one of the great works of literature of the 20th century. Book tickets months in advance, especially for July and August.',
'translations' => [
'es' => ['title' => 'Casa de Ana Frank — escondidos a plena vista', 'description' => 'Comience en la Casa de Ana Frank en el Prinsengracht — una de las experiencias museísticas más visitadas y emocionalmente poderosas de Europa. El 6 de julio de 1942, la joven Ana Frank, sus padres y su hermana se escondieron en el "Anexo Secreto" — una extensión trasera oculta del edificio, sellada detrás de una estantería móvil — para escapar de la ocupación nazi. Ocho personas vivieron en el anexo durante 761 días sin salir, sostenidas por el valor de los empleados no judíos que los escondían. El 4 de agosto de 1944, el anexo fue allanado por la Gestapo. Ana murió de tifus en Bergen-Belsen en febrero o marzo de 1945, a los 15 años. Su diario ha sido traducido a 70 idiomas y vendido más de 30 millones de ejemplares.'],
'fr' => ['title' => 'La Maison d\'Anne Frank — cachés en plein jour', 'description' => 'Commencez à la Maison d\'Anne Frank sur le Prinsengracht — l\'une des expériences muséales les plus visitées et les plus émotionnellement puissantes d\'Europe. Le 6 juillet 1942, la jeune Anne Frank, ses parents et sa sœur se cachèrent dans l\'"Annexe Secrète" — une extension arrière cachée de l\'immeuble, scellée derrière une bibliothèque mobile — pour fuir l\'occupation nazie. Huit personnes vécurent dans l\'annexe pendant 761 jours sans sortir. Le 4 août 1944, l\'annexe fut investie par la Gestapo. Anne mourut du typhus à Bergen-Belsen en février ou mars 1945, à 15 ans. Son journal a été traduit en 70 langues et vendu à plus de 30 millions d\'exemplaires.'],
'de' => ['title' => 'Anne-Frank-Haus — versteckt vor aller Augen', 'description' => 'Beginnen Sie im Anne-Frank-Haus am Prinsengracht — einem der meistbesuchten und emotional kraftvollsten Museumserlebnisse Europas. Am 6. Juli 1942 tauchte die junge Anne Frank mit ihren Eltern und ihrer Schwester im "Hinterhaus" unter — einem versteckten hinteren Anbau des Gebäudes, hinter einem beweglichen Bücherregal versiegelt — um der Nazi-Besatzung zu entkommen. Acht Menschen lebten 761 Tage im Hinterhaus, ohne hinauszugehen. Am 4. August 1944 wurde das Hinterhaus von der Gestapo gestürmt. Anne starb im Februar oder März 1945 an Typhus in Bergen-Belsen, 15 Jahre alt. Ihr Tagebuch wurde in 70 Sprachen übersetzt und über 30 Millionen Mal verkauft.'],
'it' => ['title' => 'Casa di Anna Frank — nascosti alla luce del sole', 'description' => 'Iniziate dalla Casa di Anna Frank sul Prinsengracht — una delle esperienze museali più visitate ed emotivamente potenti d\'Europa. Il 6 luglio 1942, la giovane Anna Frank, i suoi genitori e sua sorella si nascosero nell\'"Alloggio segreto" — un\'estensione posteriore nascosta dell\'edificio, sigillata dietro una libreria mobile — per sfuggire all\'occupazione nazista. Otto persone vissero nell\'alloggio per 761 giorni senza uscire. Il 4 agosto 1944, l\'alloggio fu perquisito dalla Gestapo. Anna morì di tifo a Bergen-Belsen nel febbraio o marzo 1945, a 15 anni. Il suo diario è stato tradotto in 70 lingue e venduto in oltre 30 milioni di copie.'],
