[
'title'       => 'Rijksmuseum — The Greatest Dutch Museum',
'order'       => 3,
'location'    => ['lat' => 52.3600, 'lng' => 4.8852],
'description' => 'The Rijksmuseum is the national museum of the Netherlands and one of the greatest art museums in the world, housing the most comprehensive collection of Dutch Golden Age painting in existence — which is to say, the most comprehensive collection of Rembrandt, Vermeer, Frans Hals, Jan Steen, and their contemporaries anywhere on earth. The building itself is a statement of national pride: designed by Pierre Cuypers and completed in 1885 in a neo-Gothic and neo-Renaissance style that combines the brick and stone construction of Dutch medieval architecture with elaborate polychrome tile decorations, it was the grandest public building in 19th-century Amsterdam and caused considerable controversy — critics complained it looked more like a Catholic church than a museum, in a city whose cultural identity was strongly Reformed Protestant. The collection of 8,000 objects on display (from a total of over one million in storage) spans the full breadth of Dutch cultural history from the Middle Ages to the present, but the heart of any visit must be the Gallery of Honour on the second floor, where Rembrandt\'s Night Watch hangs in its own dedicated room at the end of the central axis — a painting of such overwhelming scale (363 by 437 centimetres), drama, and technical virtuosity that it stops visitors in their tracks even after they have seen it in reproduction a thousand times. The brilliant light effects, the sense of arrested movement, the psychological complexity of the 34 figures captured in a moment of civic drama — these qualities made the Night Watch famous in Rembrandt\'s own lifetime and have never ceased to astonish. Nearby hang Vermeer\'s The Milkmaid and Woman Reading a Letter — works of such luminous stillness that they seem to vibrate with a presence that photographs cannot capture.',
'translations' => [
'es' => ['title' => 'Rijksmuseum — el mayor museo holandés', 'description' => 'El Rijksmuseum es el museo nacional de los Países Bajos y uno de los más grandes museos de arte del mundo, albergando la colección más completa de pintura de la Edad de Oro holandesa en existencia. El corazón de cualquier visita debe ser la Galería de Honor en el segundo piso, donde cuelga La Ronda Nocturna de Rembrandt en su propia sala dedicada — una pintura de escala tan abrumadora (363 por 437 centímetros), drama y virtuosismo técnico que detiene a los visitantes incluso después de haberla visto mil veces en reproducción. Cerca cuelgan La Lechera de Vermeer y Mujer Leyendo una Carta — obras de tal quietud luminosa que parecen vibrar con una presencia que las fotografías no pueden capturar.'],
'fr' => ['title' => 'Le Rijksmuseum — le plus grand musée néerlandais', 'description' => 'Le Rijksmuseum est le musée national des Pays-Bas et l\'un des plus grands musées d\'art au monde, abritant la collection la plus complète de peinture de l\'Âge d\'Or néerlandais. Le cœur de toute visite doit être la Galerie d\'Honneur au deuxième étage, où La Ronde de nuit de Rembrandt est accrochée dans sa propre salle dédiée — un tableau d\'une envergure écrasante (363 sur 437 centimètres), d\'un dramatisme et d\'une virtuosité technique qui arrêtent les visiteurs même après l\'avoir vu mille fois en reproduction. À proximité se trouvent La Laitière de Vermeer et La Femme lisant une lettre — des œuvres d\'une quiétude si lumineuse qu\'elles semblent vibrer d\'une présence que les photographies ne peuvent pas capter.'],
'de' => ['title' => 'Das Rijksmuseum — das größte niederländische Museum', 'description' => 'Das Rijksmuseum ist das Nationalmuseum der Niederlande und eines der größten Kunstmuseen der Welt, das die umfassendste Sammlung niederländischer Goldener-Zeitalter-Malerei beherbergt. Das Herzstück eines jeden Besuchs muss die Ehrengalerie im zweiten Stockwerk sein, wo Rembrandts Nachtwache in einem eigenen Saal hängt — ein Gemälde von so überwältigender Größe (363 mal 437 Zentimeter), Dramatik und technischer Virtuosität, dass es Besucher anhält, selbst nachdem sie es tausendmal in Reproduktion gesehen haben. In der Nähe hängen Vermeers Die Milchmagd und Brieflesendes Mädchen — Werke von so leuchtender Stille, dass sie mit einer Präsenz zu vibrieren scheinen, die Fotos nicht erfassen können.'],
'it' => ['title' => 'Il Rijksmuseum — il più grande museo olandese', 'description' => 'Il Rijksmuseum è il museo nazionale dei Paesi Bassi e uno dei più grandi musei d\'arte al mondo, che ospita la collezione più completa di pittura dell\'Età dell\'Oro olandese esistente. Il cuore di ogni visita deve essere la Galleria d\'Onore al secondo piano, dove La Ronda di Notte di Rembrandt è appesa nella sua sala dedicata — un dipinto di scala così travolgente (363 per 437 centimetri), dramma e virtuosismo tecnico che ferma i visitatori anche dopo averlo visto mille volte in riproduzione. Nelle vicinanze sono appese La Lattaia di Vermeer e Donna che legge una lettera — opere di tale quiete luminosa che sembrano vibrare con una presenza che le fotografie non riescono a catturare.'],
