[
'title'       => 'Van Gogh Museum — Letters to Theo',
'order'       => 4,
'location'    => ['lat' => 52.3584, 'lng' => 4.8811],
'description' => 'A five-minute walk from the Rijksmuseum stands the Van Gogh Museum, the most visited museum in the Netherlands and one of the most visited in all of Europe, housing the largest collection of works by Vincent van Gogh in the world: 200 paintings, 500 drawings, and 750 of the extraordinary letters he wrote to his younger brother Theo, which together constitute one of the most moving and intimate self-portraits an artist has ever created. Van Gogh was born in 1853 in the Dutch province of North Brabant, the son of a Protestant pastor, and spent his formative years in failure — as an art dealer, a teacher, a lay preacher, and a missionary — before, at the age of 27, resolving to become a painter. In the decade that followed, working in poverty and with an increasingly fragile mental health, he produced approximately 2,100 works, including around 860 oil paintings, almost all of which were created in the final ten years of his life. He sold precisely one painting during his lifetime. The museum follows his development chronologically, from the dark, earthy palette of his Dutch period (the extraordinary Potato Eaters) through the revelatory impact of his encounter with Impressionism in Paris, to the blinding, vibrating colour and energy of his Provençal period in Arles and Saint-Rémy — the period that produced The Bedroom, The Sower, Almond Blossom, and his extraordinary series of self-portraits. The museum also holds a significant collection of works by Van Gogh\'s contemporaries — Gauguin, Toulouse-Lautrec, Bernard — who illuminate the artistic context in which his revolutionary vision developed.',
'translations' => [
'es' => ['title' => 'Museo Van Gogh — cartas a Theo', 'description' => 'A cinco minutos del Rijksmuseum se encuentra el Museo Van Gogh, el más visitado de los Países Bajos, que alberga la mayor colección de obras de Vincent van Gogh en el mundo: 200 pinturas, 500 dibujos y 750 de las extraordinarias cartas que escribió a su hermano Theo. Van Gogh pasó sus años formativos en el fracaso antes de, a los 27 años, decidir hacerse pintor. En la década siguiente, trabajando en la pobreza con una salud mental cada vez más frágil, produjo aproximadamente 2.100 obras. Vendió exactamente una pintura durante su vida. El museo sigue su desarrollo cronológicamente, desde los Comedores de Patatas hasta el período de Provenza con La Habitación, El Sembrador y la Flor de Almendro.'],
'fr' => ['title' => 'Le Musée Van Gogh — lettres à Théo', 'description' => 'À cinq minutes du Rijksmuseum se trouve le Musée Van Gogh, le plus visité des Pays-Bas, qui abrite la plus grande collection d\'œuvres de Vincent van Gogh au monde : 200 tableaux, 500 dessins et 750 des extraordinaires lettres qu\'il écrivit à son frère Théo. Van Gogh passa ses années de formation dans l\'échec avant de décider, à 27 ans, de devenir peintre. Dans la décennie qui suivit, il produisit environ 2 100 œuvres en travaillant dans la pauvreté. Il ne vendit qu\'un seul tableau de son vivant. Le musée retrace son développement chronologiquement, des Mangeurs de pommes de terre à la période provençale avec La Chambre, Le Semeur et la Branche d\'amandier en fleurs.'],
'de' => ['title' => 'Van-Gogh-Museum — Briefe an Theo', 'description' => 'Fünf Minuten vom Rijksmuseum entfernt steht das Van-Gogh-Museum, das meistbesuchte Museum der Niederlande, das die größte Sammlung von Werken von Vincent van Gogh der Welt beherbergt: 200 Gemälde, 500 Zeichnungen und 750 der außergewöhnlichen Briefe, die er an seinen Bruder Theo schrieb. Van Gogh verbrachte seine prägenden Jahre im Scheitern, bevor er mit 27 Jahren beschloss, Maler zu werden. In dem folgenden Jahrzehnt schuf er in Armut etwa 2.100 Werke. Er verkaufte zu Lebzeiten genau ein Gemälde. Das Museum verfolgt seine Entwicklung chronologisch, von den Kartoffelessern bis zur Provence-Periode mit dem Schlafzimmer, dem Sämann und dem Mandelblüten-Gemälde.'],
'it' => ['title' => 'Museo Van Gogh — lettere a Theo', 'description' => 'A cinque minuti dal Rijksmuseum si trova il Museo Van Gogh, il più visitato dei Paesi Bassi, che ospita la più grande collezione di opere di Vincent van Gogh al mondo: 200 dipinti, 500 disegni e 750 delle straordinarie lettere che scrisse al fratello Theo. Van Gogh trascorse i suoi anni formativi nel fallimento prima di decidere, a 27 anni, di diventare pittore. Nel decennio successivo, lavorando in povertà, produsse circa 2.100 opere. Vendette esattamente un dipinto durante la sua vita. Il museo segue il suo sviluppo cronologicamente, dai Mangiatori di Patate al periodo provenzale con La Camera da Letto, Il Seminatore e il Mandorlo in Fiore.'],
],
