[
'title'       => 'Alfama & São Jorge Castle — The Moorish City',
'order'       => 1,
'location'    => ['lat' => 38.7139, 'lng' => -9.1334],
'description' => 'Begin your Lisbon tour in the Alfama, the oldest neighbourhood in the city and the only district to survive the 1755 earthquake largely intact — its irregular, labyrinthine street pattern is a direct inheritance from the Moorish city that preceded the Christian reconquest, and wandering its alleys of whitewashed houses hung with laundry and bougainvillea feels like stepping several centuries backwards in time. The Moors — Arab and Berber forces from North Africa — captured Lisbon in 714 AD and held it for over four centuries until Alfonso I of Portugal conquered the city in 1147 with the assistance of crusaders en route to the Holy Land. The Alfama takes its name from the Arabic "al-hamma" meaning hot springs, a reference to the thermal baths that served the medieval Moorish city. Climb to the Castelo de São Jorge — the fortress of Saint George — which crowns the highest hill in the old city at 120 metres, offering the finest panoramic views of Lisbon, the Tagus, and on clear days the southern hills of the Alentejo across the river. The castle was originally a Moorish alcazaba (fortified palace) of the 11th century; its current walls are largely a medieval Christian rebuilding of the 12th century, though significantly altered and romantically "medievalized" in the 1940s during the Estado Novo dictatorship — a fact that contemporary Portuguese historians note with some embarrassment. Within the castle walls, the ruins of the medieval royal palace where King Manuel I was born in 1469 are visible, as are archaeological excavations revealing Bronze Age, Iron Age, and Roman occupation of the site stretching back 2,800 years.',
'translations' => [
'es' => ['title' => 'Alfama y el Castillo de São Jorge — la ciudad mora', 'description' => 'Comience su tour por Lisboa en la Alfama, el barrio más antiguo de la ciudad y el único que sobrevivió al terremoto de 1755 en gran parte intacto — su irregular patrón de calles laberínticas es una herencia directa de la ciudad mora que precedió a la Reconquista cristiana. Los moros capturaron Lisboa en 714 d.C. y la sostuvieron durante más de cuatro siglos hasta que Alfonso I de Portugal conquistó la ciudad en 1147. El Castillo de São Jorge corona la colina más alta de la ciudad antigua a 120 metros, ofreciendo las mejores vistas panorámicas de Lisboa y el Tajo. Dentro de los muros del castillo, son visibles las ruinas del palacio real medieval donde nació el Rey Manuel I en 1469.'],
'fr' => ['title' => 'L\'Alfama et le Château de São Jorge — la ville maure', 'description' => 'Commencez votre visite de Lisbonne dans l\'Alfama, le quartier le plus ancien de la ville et le seul à avoir survécu au tremblement de terre de 1755 en grande partie intact — son plan de rue labyrinthique et irrégulier est un héritage direct de la ville maure qui précéda la reconquête chrétienne. Les Maures s\'emparèrent de Lisbonne en 714 apr. J.-C. et la tinrent pendant plus de quatre siècles jusqu\'à la conquête par Alphonse Ier du Portugal en 1147. Le Château de São Jorge couronne la plus haute colline de la vieille ville à 120 mètres, offrant les plus belles vues panoramiques sur Lisbonne et le Tage.'],
'de' => ['title' => 'Alfama & Burg São Jorge — die maurische Stadt', 'description' => 'Beginnen Sie Ihre Lissabon-Tour im Alfama, dem ältesten Viertel der Stadt und dem einzigen, das das Erdbeben von 1755 weitgehend unversehrt überstand — sein unregelmäßiges, labyrinthisches Straßenmuster ist ein direktes Erbe der maurischen Stadt, die der christlichen Rückeroberung vorausging. Die Mauren eroberten Lissabon 714 n. Chr. und hielten es über vier Jahrhunderte lang, bis Alfonso I. von Portugal die Stadt 1147 einnahm. Die Burg São Jorge krönt den höchsten Hügel der Altstadt auf 120 Metern und bietet die schönsten Panoramablicke auf Lissabon und den Tejo.'],
'it' => ['title' => 'Alfama e il Castello di São Jorge — la città moresca', 'description' => 'Iniziate il vostro tour di Lisbona nell\'Alfama, il quartiere più antico della città e l\'unico a sopravvivere al terremoto del 1755 in gran parte intatto — il suo schema stradale labirintico e irregolare è un\'eredità diretta della città moresca che precedette la riconquista cristiana. I Mori catturarono Lisbona nel 714 d.C. e la tennero per oltre quattro secoli fino alla conquista di Alfonso I del Portogallo nel 1147. Il Castello di São Jorge incorona la collina più alta della città antica a 120 metri, offrendo le più belle viste panoramiche di Lisbona e del Tago.'],
],
],
[
'title'       => 'Mosteiro dos Jerónimos — Marvel of Manueline Architecture',
'order'       => 2,
'location'    => ['lat' => 38.6979, 'lng' => -9.2065],
'description' => 'Take the tram or a brief taxi to Belém, the riverside district west of the city centre where Vasco da Gama\'s fleet departed for India in 1497 and where the most spectacular monument of Portuguese imperial glory survives in extraordinary condition: the Mosteiro dos Jerónimos, the Hieronymite Monastery, begun in 1501 under King Manuel I and funded directly by the profits of the spice trade with India. The Jerónimos Monastery is the supreme expression of Manueline architecture — the distinctively Portuguese late Gothic style named after King Manuel I that developed in the first decades of the 16th century as Portugal\'s astonishing wealth from the spice trade was channelled into the most ambitious building programme in the country\'s history. Manueline architecture is characterised by the incorporation of maritime imagery — ropes, coral, anchors, sea monsters, armillary spheres — into the decorative vocabulary of Gothic stone carving, producing buildings that seem to celebrate the sea and Portugal\'s oceanic destiny in every surface detail. The south portal of the Jerónimos, facing the Tagus, is possibly the most lavishly decorated stone doorway in the world: every centimetre of its surface is carved in the most intricate detail. The cloisters are the most beautiful in Portugal and among the finest in all of Europe — a double-storey structure of extraordinary delicacy in which the upper story appears almost impossibly light, its tracery columns appearing to dissolve into lace. The tombs of Vasco da Gama and the poet Luís de Camões — who immortalised the Age of Discovery in his epic Os Lusíadas — rest in the church.',
'translations' => [
'es' => ['title' => 'Mosteiro dos Jerónimos — maravilla de la arquitectura manuelina', 'description' => 'Tome el tranvía o un taxi hasta Belém, el barrio ribereño al oeste del centro de la ciudad donde la flota de Vasco de Gama partió hacia India en 1497. El Mosteiro dos Jerónimos, comenzado en 1501 bajo el Rey Manuel I y financiado con los beneficios del comercio de especias con India, es la suprema expresión de la arquitectura manuelina — el distintivo estilo gótico tardío portugués que incorpora imágenes marítimas en cada detalle decorativo. El portal sur del Jerónimos, posiblemente la portada de piedra más lujosamente decorada del mundo, y los claustros, los más bellos de Portugal, albergan las tumbas de Vasco de Gama y el poeta Luís de Camões.'],
'fr' => ['title' => 'Mosteiro dos Jerónimos — merveille de l\'architecture manuéline', 'description' => 'Prenez le tramway ou un taxi jusqu\'à Belém, le quartier riverain à l\'ouest du centre-ville, d\'où la flotte de Vasco de Gama est partie pour l\'Inde en 1497. Le Mosteiro dos Jerónimos, commencé en 1501 sous le roi Manuel Ier et financé par les bénéfices du commerce des épices avec l\'Inde, est l\'expression suprême de l\'architecture manuéline — ce style gothique tardif distinctivement portugais qui incorpore des images maritimes dans chaque détail décoratif. Le portail sud des Jerónimos, peut-être la porte en pierre la plus richement décorée au monde, et les cloîtres, les plus beaux du Portugal, abritent les tombeaux de Vasco de Gama et du poète Luís de Camões.'],
'de' => ['title' => 'Mosteiro dos Jerónimos — Wunderwerk der manuelinischen Architektur', 'description' => 'Nehmen Sie die Straßenbahn oder ein Taxi nach Belém, dem Flussviertel westlich des Stadtzentrums, von wo aus Vasco da Gamas Flotte 1497 nach Indien aufbrach. Das Mosteiro dos Jerónimos, 1501 unter König Manuel I. begonnen und direkt durch die Gewinne des Gewürzhandels mit Indien finanziert, ist der höchste Ausdruck der manuelinischen Architektur — des charakteristisch portugiesischen Spätstils, der maritime Bildsprache in jedes dekorative Detail einbezieht. Das Südportal des Jerónimos, möglicherweise das aufwendigst dekorierte Steinportal der Welt, und die Kreuzgänge, die schönsten Portugals, beherbergen die Gräber von Vasco da Gama und dem Dichter Luís de Camões.'],
'it' => ['title' => 'Mosteiro dos Jerónimos — meraviglia dell\'architettura manuelina', 'description' => 'Prendete il tram o un taxi fino a Belém, il quartiere fluviale a ovest del centro città da dove la flotta di Vasco da Gama partì per l\'India nel 1497. Il Mosteiro dos Jerónimos, iniziato nel 1501 sotto il Re Manuel I e finanziato direttamente con i profitti del commercio delle spezie con l\'India, è la suprema espressione dell\'architettura manuelina — il distintivo stile gotico tardivo portoghese che incorpora immagini marittime in ogni dettaglio decorativo. Il portale sud dei Jerónimos, probabilmente il portale in pietra più riccamente decorato al mondo, e i chiostri, i più belli del Portogallo, ospitano le tombe di Vasco da Gama e del poeta Luís de Camões.'],
],
],
[
'title'       => 'Museu Nacional do Azulejo — The Art of the Tile',
'order'       => 3,
'location'    => ['lat' => 38.7241, 'lng' => -9.1174],
'description' => 'No visit to Lisbon is complete without an immersion in the art of the azulejo — the glazed ceramic tile that covers the facades, interiors, churches, stations, and palaces of Portugal with a lavishness found nowhere else in the world. The word "azulejo" comes from the Arabic "az-zulayj" meaning polished stone, and the tradition of using glazed tiles to decorate buildings arrived in Portugal from Moorish Andalusia in the late 15th century, reaching the country at almost exactly the moment when the Age of Discovery was generating the wealth to implement it on an unprecedented scale. The Museu Nacional do Azulejo, housed in the former convent of Madre de Deus (founded 1509), is the finest museum dedicated to this art form and contains examples spanning five centuries of tile production, from the earliest Moorish geometric patterns through the narrative blue-and-white panels of the 17th and 18th centuries — when Portuguese azulejaria reached its artistic peak — to the modernist and contemporary works of the 20th and 21st centuries. The collection\'s most spectacular single piece is a 23-metre panoramic panel depicting Lisbon as it appeared before the 1755 earthquake — a ghostly, magnificent record of the city that no longer exists, showing in extraordinary detail the streets, buildings, waterfront, and daily life of 18th-century Lisbon. The convent church itself is a masterpiece of decorative arts: its walls, ceiling, and chancel are entirely covered in blue-and-white azulejo panels and gilded woodcarving of extraordinary quality.',
'translations' => [
'es' => ['title' => 'Museu Nacional do Azulejo — el arte del azulejo', 'description' => 'Ninguna visita a Lisboa está completa sin una inmersión en el arte del azulejo — la baldosa cerámica vidriada que cubre las fachadas, interiores, iglesias, estaciones y palacios de Portugal con una generosidad única en el mundo. El Museu Nacional do Azulejo, alojado en el antiguo convento de Madre de Deus (fundado en 1509), contiene ejemplos que abarcan cinco siglos de producción de azulejos. La pieza individual más espectacular es un panel panorámico de 23 metros que muestra Lisboa tal como era antes del terremoto de 1755 — un registro fantasmal y magnífico de la ciudad que ya no existe.'],
'fr' => ['title' => 'Museu Nacional do Azulejo — l\'art de l\'azulejo', 'description' => 'Aucune visite de Lisbonne n\'est complète sans une immersion dans l\'art de l\'azulejo — le carrelage en céramique vernissée qui recouvre les façades, intérieurs, églises, gares et palais du Portugal avec une générosité que l\'on ne trouve nulle part ailleurs au monde. Le Museu Nacional do Azulejo, logé dans l\'ancien couvent de Madre de Deus (fondé en 1509), contient des exemples couvrant cinq siècles de production d\'azulejos. La pièce individuelle la plus spectaculaire est un panneau panoramique de 23 mètres montrant Lisbonne telle qu\'elle était avant le tremblement de terre de 1755 — un record fantomatique et magnifique de la ville qui n\'existe plus.'],
'de' => ['title' => 'Museu Nacional do Azulejo — die Kunst der Kachel', 'description' => 'Kein Lissabon-Besuch ist vollständig ohne ein Eintauchen in die Kunst des Azulejo — die glasierte Keramikfliese, die die Fassaden, Innenräume, Kirchen, Bahnhöfe und Paläste Portugals mit einer Üppigkeit bedeckt, die nirgendwo sonst auf der Welt zu finden ist. Das Museu Nacional do Azulejo, untergebracht im ehemaligen Kloster Madre de Deus (gegründet 1509), enthält Beispiele aus fünf Jahrhunderten der Fliesenproduktion. Das spektakulärste Einzelstück ist ein 23 Meter langes Panoramapaneel, das Lissabon zeigt, wie es vor dem Erdbeben von 1755 aussah — ein gespenstisches, prächtiges Zeugnis der Stadt, die nicht mehr existiert.'],
'it' => ['title' => 'Museu Nacional do Azulejo — l\'arte delle piastrelle', 'description' => 'Nessuna visita a Lisbona è completa senza un\'immersione nell\'arte dell\'azulejo — la piastrella in ceramica smaltata che ricopre le facciate, gli interni, le chiese, le stazioni e i palazzi del Portogallo con una generosità che non si trova da nessun\'altra parte al mondo. Il Museu Nacional do Azulejo, ospitato nell\'ex convento di Madre de Deus (fondato nel 1509), contiene esempi che abbracciano cinque secoli di produzione di azulejos. Il pezzo singolo più spettacolare è un pannello panoramico di 23 metri che mostra Lisbona com\'era prima del terremoto del 1755 — un registro spettrale e magnifico della città che non esiste più.'],
],
],
[
'title'       => 'LX Factory — Reinventing Industrial Lisbon',
'order'       => 4,
'location'    => ['lat' => 38.7041, 'lng' => -9.1774],
'description' => 'Below the iconic 25th of April Bridge — the great suspension bridge across the Tagus completed in 1966 that was modelled on San Francisco\'s Golden Gate and whose uncanny resemblance to it has caused many visitors to perform a startled double-take — the LX Factory occupies a former 19th-century industrial complex of rope and textile factories covering 23,000 square metres on the riverside at Alcântara. Opened as a creative hub in 2008, the LX Factory has become one of Lisbon\'s most characterful and visited attractions: a permanent market-cum-creative village in which graphic design studios, independent bookshops (the extraordinary Ler Devagar — "Read Slowly" — with its bikes suspended from the ceiling and books stacked to the rafters is one of the finest bookshops in Europe), fashion ateliers, craft workshops, recording studios, restaurants, and bars occupy the high-ceilinged, industrial brick spaces with a looseness and creativity that feels genuinely alive rather than curated. Every Sunday the LX Factory hosts a market that has become one of the best flea and artisan markets in Portugal: vintage furniture, antique books, vinyl records, ceramics, plants, street food, and live music fill the complex from 10am to 6pm. The restaurant scene has also developed remarkably, with several of Lisbon\'s most interesting chefs choosing the atmospheric industrial spaces here over more conventional restaurant locations — in particular the Sunday brunch at the Cantina LX is a Lisbon institution not to be missed.',
'translations' => [
'es' => ['title' => 'LX Factory — reinventando el Lisboa industrial', 'description' => 'Bajo el icónico Puente del 25 de Abril, la LX Factory ocupa un antiguo complejo industrial del siglo XIX de 23.000 metros cuadrados en la orilla del Tajo en Alcântara. Inaugurada como hub creativo en 2008, se ha convertido en una de las atracciones más características de Lisboa: un mercado permanente-aldea creativa en el que estudios de diseño gráfico, librerías independientes (la extraordinaria Ler Devagar — "Leer Despacio" — es una de las mejores librerías de Europa), talleres artesanales y restaurantes ocupan los espacios de ladrillo industrial. Cada domingo, la LX Factory celebra un mercado que se ha convertido en uno de los mejores mercados de pulgas y artesanos de Portugal.'],
'fr' => ['title' => 'LX Factory — réinventer le Lisbonne industriel', 'description' => 'Sous l\'emblématique Pont du 25 Avril, la LX Factory occupe un ancien complexe industriel du XIXe siècle de 23 000 mètres carrés sur les bords du Tage à Alcântara. Ouverte comme hub créatif en 2008, elle est devenue l\'une des attractions les plus caractéristiques de Lisbonne : un marché permanent-village créatif dans lequel des studios de design graphique, des librairies indépendantes (l\'extraordinaire Ler Devagar — "Lire Lentement" — est l\'une des meilleures librairies d\'Europe), des ateliers artisanaux et des restaurants occupent les espaces de brique industrielle. Chaque dimanche, la LX Factory accueille un marché devenu l\'un des meilleurs marchés aux puces et marchés artisanaux du Portugal.'],
'de' => ['title' => 'LX Factory — das industrielle Lissabon neu erfinden', 'description' => 'Unterhalb der ikonischen Brücke vom 25. April belegt die LX Factory einen ehemaligen industriellen Komplex aus dem 19. Jahrhundert mit 23.000 Quadratmetern am Tejo-Ufer in Alcântara. 2008 als kreatives Zentrum eröffnet, ist sie zu einer der charaktervollsten Attraktionen Lissabons geworden: eine permanente Markt-cum-Kreativdorf-Anlage, in der Grafikdesignstudios, unabhängige Buchhandlungen (das außergewöhnliche Ler Devagar — "Langsam Lesen" — ist eine der feinsten Buchhandlungen Europas), Handwerksateliers und Restaurants die industriellen Backsteinräume beleben. Jeden Sonntag veranstaltet die LX Factory einen Markt, der zu einem der besten Floh- und Handwerksmärkte Portugals geworden ist.'],
'it' => ['title' => 'LX Factory — reinventare la Lisbona industriale', 'description' => 'Sotto l\'iconico Ponte del 25 Aprile, la LX Factory occupa un ex complesso industriale dell\'Ottocento di 23.000 metri quadrati sul lungofiume di Alcântara. Aperta come hub creativo nel 2008, è diventata una delle attrazioni più caratteristiche di Lisbona: un mercato permanente-villaggio creativo in cui studi di design grafico, librerie indipendenti (la straordinaria Ler Devagar — "Leggi Lentamente" — è una delle migliori librerie d\'Europa), atelier artigianali e ristoranti occupano gli spazi di mattoni industriali. Ogni domenica la LX Factory ospita un mercato diventato uno dei migliori mercati delle pulci e dell\'artigianato in Portogallo.'],
],
],
[
'title'       => 'Fado at a Casa de Fado — The Sound of Saudade',
'order'       => 5,
'location'    => ['lat' => 38.7113, 'lng' => -9.1371],
'description' => 'No tour of Lisbon is complete without an evening of fado — the music that is to Portugal what flamenco is to Andalusia, what tango is to Buenos Aires, what blues is to the American South: the sound of a people expressing the full weight of their experience in music of overwhelming emotional directness. The word "fado" comes from the Latin "fatum" meaning fate or destiny, and the music itself is characterised by the concept of saudade — an untranslatable Portuguese word that combines nostalgia, longing, loss, absence, and the bittersweet awareness that what was loved may be irrecoverably gone. Fado is believed to have developed in Lisbon\'s working-class neighbourhoods — particularly the Mouraria and the Alfama — in the early 19th century, though its roots are complex and probably include influences from African rhythms brought by enslaved people, Brazilian modinha songs, and the musical traditions of the Moorish city. The canonical form consists of a solo singer (fadista) accompanied by two instruments: the Portuguese guitarra (a twelve-string round-backed instrument related to the cittern, with a sound quite unlike any other guitar in the world) and the viola baixo (a standard acoustic guitar providing rhythmic accompaniment). The greatest fado singer of the 20th century, Amália Rodrigues — known simply as "a Rainha" (the Queen) — elevated the form to international recognition between the 1940s and her death in 1999, and her recordings remain the essential introduction to the tradition. The best casas de fado are in the Alfama and Mouraria: look for smaller, family-run venues where local fadistas perform rather than the larger tourist-oriented restaurants.',
'translations' => [
'es' => ['title' => 'Fado en una Casa de Fado — el sonido de la saudade', 'description' => 'Ningún tour por Lisboa está completo sin una velada de fado — la música que es a Portugal lo que el flamenco a Andalucía o el tango a Buenos Aires. La palabra "fado" viene del latín "fatum" que significa destino, y la música se caracteriza por el concepto de saudade — una palabra portuguesa intraducible que combina nostalgia, anhelo, pérdida y la agridulce conciencia de que lo amado puede estar irremediablemente perdido. La gran intérprete del siglo XX, Amália Rodrigues — conocida simplemente como "a Rainha" (la Reina) — elevó el género al reconocimiento internacional entre los años 40 y su muerte en 1999. Las mejores casas de fado están en el Alfama y la Mouraria.'],
'fr' => ['title' => 'Le Fado dans une Casa de Fado — le son de la saudade', 'description' => 'Aucune visite de Lisbonne n\'est complète sans une soirée de fado — la musique qui est au Portugal ce que le flamenco est à l\'Andalousie ou le tango à Buenos Aires. Le mot "fado" vient du latin "fatum" signifiant destin, et la musique se caractérise par le concept de saudade — un mot portugais intraduisible qui combine nostalgie, désir, perte et l\'amère conscience que ce qu\'on a aimé pourrait être irrémédiablement perdu. La grande interprète du XXe siècle, Amália Rodrigues — connue simplement comme "a Rainha" (la Reine) — a élevé le genre à la reconnaissance internationale entre les années 40 et sa mort en 1999. Les meilleures casas de fado se trouvent dans l\'Alfama et la Mouraria.'],
'de' => ['title' => 'Fado in einer Casa de Fado — der Klang der Saudade', 'description' => 'Kein Lissabon-Tour ist vollständig ohne einen Fado-Abend — die Musik, die für Portugal das ist, was Flamenco für Andalusien oder Tango für Buenos Aires ist. Das Wort "Fado" kommt vom lateinischen "fatum" für Schicksal, und die Musik ist von dem Konzept der Saudade geprägt — einem unübersetzbaren portugiesischen Wort, das Nostalgie, Sehnsucht, Verlust und das bittersüße Bewusstsein vereint, dass das Geliebte unwiederbringlich verloren sein könnte. Die große Interpretin des 20. Jahrhunderts, Amália Rodrigues — bekannt einfach als "a Rainha" (die Königin) — hob das Genre zur internationalen Anerkennung. Die besten Casas de Fado sind im Alfama und in der Mouraria.'],
'it' => ['title' => 'Fado in una Casa de Fado — il suono della saudade', 'description' => 'Nessun tour di Lisbona è completo senza una serata di fado — la musica che è al Portogallo ciò che il flamenco è all\'Andalusia o il tango a Buenos Aires. La parola "fado" viene dal latino "fatum" che significa destino, e la musica è caratterizzata dal concetto di saudade — una parola portoghese intraducibile che combina nostalgia, desiderio, perdita e la dolceamara consapevolezza che ciò che era amato potrebbe essere irrimediabilmente perduto. La grande interprete del XX secolo, Amália Rodrigues — nota semplicemente come "a Rainha" (la Regina) — elevò il genere al riconoscimento internazionale. Le migliori case di fado si trovano nell\'Alfama e nella Mouraria.'],
],
],
],
];

